            <pb xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                n="20"
                xml:id="pb-20"
                facs="#i20"/>
            <lb/>
This last passage is one of the few<lb/>
philosophical ones in his work<del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">s</del> the<lb/>
most worthy of notice: his pages are<lb/>
generally filled with the grossest absurdities<lb/>
It is difficult to conjecture from them<lb/>
whether he is self deluded or whether<lb/>
he is endeavouring to deceive others<lb/>
whether his imagination was distempered<lb/>
or whether he was attempting an<lb/>
imposture<lb/>
