                type="person">
               <name xml:id="tag36" type="person">
          Agrippa
        </name>
            </rs> was born at <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag37"
                ref="#place_1312"
                type="place">
               <name xml:id="tag37" type="place">
          Cologne
        </name>
            </rs> in 1463<lb/>
after the publication of his system<lb/>
he was of course considered as a Magician<lb/>
by the vulgar and a number of idle<lb/>
            <lb/>
            <pb xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                n="21"
                xml:id="pb-21"
                facs="#i21"/>
            <lb/>
tales exist with regard to his History<lb/>
He asserted that He was in possession of<lb/>
the <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
