16 century. His work on the metals<lb/>
contain a number of important <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">facts</del>
            <lb/>
truths which are always detailed with<lb/>
peculiar candour and modesty -<lb/>
He describes the general <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">position</hi> of<lb/>
the veins in the great mineral<lb/>
countries of <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag60"
                ref="#place_324"
                type="place">
               <name xml:id="tag60" type="place">
          Germany
        </name>
            </rs>.<lb/>
He gives a natural history of ores and<lb/>
a particular account of the manner<lb/>
in which the are worked and in <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">none</hi>
            <lb/>
            <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">of his details </hi>does He enter upon<lb/>
            <lb/>
            <pb xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                n="31"
                xml:id="pb-31"
                facs="#i31"/>
            <lb/>
wild speculations and He has treated the<lb/>
professed adepts of his age with a cool<lb/>
and dignified <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">un</del> indifference. -<lb/>
            <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag61"
                ref="#person_1059"
                type="person">
               <name xml:id="tag61" type="person">
          Lazarus Erckern
        </name>
            </rs> assay Master General<lb/>
to the German mines was Co<add xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0">n</add>temporary <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">with</hi>
            <lb/>
            <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">
               <rs xml:id="ttag62" ref="#person_062" type="person">
                  <name xml:id="tag62" type="person">
          Agricola
        </name>
               </rs>
            </hi>. His work on the art of assaying<lb/>
has been translated into English by <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag63"
                ref="#person_1060"
                type="person">
               <name xml:id="tag63" type="person">
          Sir<lb/>John Pettus
        </name>
            </rs> and it contains much<lb/>
valuable matter with regard to metallur-<lb/>
