            <lb/>
            <pb xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                n="48"
                xml:id="pb-48"
                facs="#i48"/>
            <lb/>
            <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">through the Atmosphere loaded with</hi>
            <lb/>
            <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">aqueous</hi> vapour -<lb/>
By the first cause He explains the<lb/>
passage in <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag88"
                ref="#otherwork_281"
                type="otherwork">
               <bibl xml:id="tag88">
            Geneis
        </bibl>
            </rs> "The fountains of the<lb/>
great deep were broken up and by the<lb/>
second the other sentence the windows<lb/>
of heaven were opened and the rain<lb/>
was upon the Earth for forty days<lb/>
and forty Nights.-<lb/>
            <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag89"
                ref="#person_1005"
                type="person">
               <name xml:id="tag89" type="person">
          Leibnitz
        </name>
            </rs> supposes that the principal<lb/>
changes which have taken place since<lb/>
            <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">the deluge</hi> have depended either upon<lb/>
Volcanic fires: or great inundations<lb/>
from the Ocean and He conceives<lb/>
            <lb/>
            <pb xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                n="49"
                xml:id="pb-49"
                facs="#i49"/>
            <lb/>
that fire and Water are Counterballancing<lb/>
powers by which an order of things<lb/>
similar to the present will be maintained<lb/>
