                type="person">
               <name xml:id="tag92" type="person">
          M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Dutens.-
        </name>
            </rs>
            <lb/>
The work it self is in the highest degree<lb/>
deserving of a minute examination -<lb/>
It is worthy of the Genius of the Illustrious<lb/>
Author:-<lb/>
When facts are stated in it they are<lb/>
detailed with clearness and accuracy<lb/>
and where Hypotheses are indulged<lb/>
            <lb/>
            <pb xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                n="50"
                xml:id="pb-50"
                facs="#i50"/>
            <lb/>
in; they mark an imagination fertile<lb/>
in novelty and pregnant with<lb/>
bold conceptions.-<lb/>
That his <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">reasoning is not always</hi> convincing<lb/>
rater depends upon his endeavouring to<lb/>
resolve problems concerning which there<lb/>
no data than upon any imperfection<lb/>
in his methods -<lb/>
The subject which He has undertaken<lb/>
            <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">to discuss</hi> is one almost above the powers<lb/>
of the human mind.<lb/>
It required high talents to produce<lb/>
any philosophical views with regard<lb/>
to it and the abilities of <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">Lebn</del>
            <lb/>
            <lb/>
            <pb xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                n="51"
                xml:id="pb-51"
                facs="#i51"/>
            <lb/>
            <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
